<DOC><DOCNO> WSJ861224-0118 </DOCNO><HL> Gulf andamp; Western Inc. UnitCloses Infosearch Purchase</HL><DD> 12/24/86</DD><SO> WALL STREET JOURNAL (J)</SO><IN> GWTENDER OFFERS, MERGERS, ACQUISITIONS (TNM) </IN><DATELINE> NEW YORK  </DATELINE><TEXT>   Gulf andamp; Western Inc.'s Simon andamp; Schuster Inc. publishing unit said it completed its acquisition of Infosearch. Terms weren't disclosed.    Infosearch provides document searches and filing services for law firms and financial institutions. Simon andamp; Schuster said it purchased Infosearch to complement other similar holdings.    Infosearch, based in Albany, N.Y., will become part of a new Simon andamp; Schuster division, Prentice Hall Legal andamp; Financial Services. Neil Campolungo, formerly president of Infosearch, will become president of the new division. </TEXT></DOC>